\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Relations now continue inside the vertex
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A relation does not only connect two fields externally.
 It modifies them internally.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So instead of only writing:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
R(A,B)
\]

\end_inset

